# ☀️ Instant Weather Checker

A lightning-fast Python script that fetches current weather data for any city.

```bash
Enter city name: Tokyo
Weather in Tokyo: +22°C Partly cloudy
🚀 Quick Start
Run Locally
Ensure Python 3.x is installed

Install dependencies:

bash
Copy
pip install requests
Run the script:

bash
Copy
python weather.py
Run in Google Colab
Open in Colab

🌟 Features
Real-time weather data

No API keys required

Works worldwide

Ultra-lightweight (3 lines of core code)

🛠️ How It Works
The script uses the free wttr.in API:

Takes city name as input

Fetches weather data

Displays temperature and conditions

📝 Example Outputs
Copy
Enter city name: Paris
Weather in Paris: +18°C Light rain

Enter city name: New York
Weather in New York: +10°C Sunny
📚 Customization Options
python
Copy
# Get temperature only
url = f"http://wttr.in/{city}?format=%t"

# Get full weather report (ASCII art)
print(requests.get(f"http://wttr.in/{city}").text)
